         <div class="col-md-12">
    <p class="text-justify">
                    <p> Scientists from Manipur have found a new plant species of 'Cherry Blossom' and as a mark of respect and for the outstanding contributions of scientist Dr Dinabandhu Sahoo, they named the new plant species as 'Prunus dinabandhuana'.The new plants grow up to 25-30 meters in dense mixed evergreen forest and unlike Japanese cherry blossoms which bloom during March-April, this new species bloom in November. This is a rare honour for any Indian to be named after a Cherry species."</p>
    </div>

